## 0. PRODUCT VISION

This app manages:
- tooling projects (tools)
- parts inside tools
- operations on parts
- procurement (materials/components)
- outsourcing (laser, gundrill, etc.)

The core of the system is:
Tool → Section → Part → Operations

---

## 1. FINAL DOMAIN MODEL

### Family
- groups similar tools (e.g. M700)
- can have attachments (product drawings)

### Tool
- projectName (e.g. M700x50)
- familyId
- dueDate
- status: Active / On Hold / Completed / Cancelled
- notes

### Section (fixed values)
- N/A
- Mould
- Plug Assist
- Anvil
- Cutter
- PnP
- Pusher

No free text sections.

---

### Part (MAIN WORK UNIT)

Each Part must have:

- toolId
- section
- name
- qty
- material
- size
- thickness
- drawingRef
- supplierId (optional)
- requiresLaser (boolean)
- notes

---

### Attachment

Attachable to:
- Family
- Part

Types:
- DXF
- PDF
- STEP
- IMAGE
- OTHER

Must support file picker (not manual path input).

---

## 2. OPERATIONS (CRITICAL — FINAL RULES)

Each Part has Operations.

We define EXACTLY 3 types:

---

### A. INTERNAL

Examples:
- CAM
- Milling
- Finish
- Assembly
- Inspection

Rules:
- controlled by user
- checkbox only
- states:
  - not done
  - done
- NO dropdown
- NO "In Progress", "Ready", "Installed"

---

### B. PROCUREMENT

Example:
- Order Material

Rules:
- NO manual status
- NO checkbox
- NO dropdown

Status comes ONLY from linked Order.

Visible states:
- Not Ordered
- Ordered
- Received

If NOT linked:
- show "Not Ordered"
- show:
  - Create Order
  - Link Order

If linked:
- show:
  - status badge
  - supplier
  - ETA
  - Open Order

---

### C. OUTSOURCE

Examples:
- Laser
- Gundrill
- Heat Treatment

Rules:
- NO internal statuses
- NO procurement statuses

Status comes from OutsourceJob:

- Pending
- Sent
- In Progress
- Done
- Cancelled

UI:
- badge/dropdown
- actions:
  - Create Job
  - Link Job
  - Open Job

---

## 3. SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH

INTERNAL → checkbox  
PROCUREMENT → Order  
OUTSOURCE → OutsourceJob  

NO overlap.

NO manual overrides.

---

## 4. PROCUREMENT MODEL

We use:

Order + OrderItem

### Order
- supplierId
- status: Not Ordered / Ordered / Received / Cancelled
- eta
- poNumber
- supplierQuoteRef
- notes

### OrderItem
- orderId
- partId
- qty
- notes

RULE:
- one Order = one Tool (enforced in UI)

---

## 5. OUTSOURCING MODEL

Separate from procurement.

### OutsourceJob
- partId
- supplierId / company
- processType
- status
- eta
- sentDate
- returnedDate
- externalJobRef
- notes

---

## 6. BLOCKERS (FINAL LOGIC)

Part is BLOCKED if:

- procurement op exists and status != Received
- outsource op exists and status != Done
- previous internal op is not done

---

## 7. NEXT ACTION (CRITICAL RULE)

Next Action must reflect REAL dependency:

Priority:

1. Procurement (Order Material)
2. Outsourcing
3. Internal operations

NEVER suggest CAM if material is not ordered.

---

## 8. TOOL PAGE = MAIN WORKSCREEN

This is the command center.

Must contain:

- summary (progress, blocked, orders, outsourcing)
- Blockers
- Next Actions
- Procurement (for this tool)
- Outsourcing (for this tool)
- Sections
- Parts

This is where daily work happens.

